# Canonical spelling for the identity that maintains this repository.
#
# A squash merge records the GitHub profile display name rather than the local git
# config, so a merged pull request can land under a different spelling of the same
# person than a local commit does. These entries collapse those spellings.
#
# Every mapping here stays within one identity. Mapping one identity onto another
# would misstate who wrote the code, so it is never done.
#
# The canonical address is on the organization domain. The commit identity moved
# there under ORG-ADR-004, and the move is forward-only: a published commit is
# never rewritten, so the earlier address stays in history and is collapsed here
# instead. Both domains therefore appear below, and both carry the profile
# spelling a squash merge stamps.

athexweb3 <athexweb3@nirapod.org> Athex Web3 <athexweb3@nirapod.org>
athexweb3 <athexweb3@nirapod.org> <athexweb3@gmail.com>
athexweb3 <athexweb3@nirapod.org> Athex Web3 <athexweb3@gmail.com>
athexweb3 <athexweb3@nirapod.org> <athexweb3@users.noreply.github.com>
